                <div id="articleTwoCopy">
                    <h2>Coming together, at a safe distance</h2>
                    <p>With social distancing coming into force around the world (in response to COVID-19) people are
                        finding creative ways to keep traditions going. In Germany religious sites such as churches and
                        mosques remain closed, so a group of Muslims approached IKEA with a unique request -- to use
                        their
                        car park to pray on Eid al-Fitr. This allowed worshippers to come together on a holy day in a
                        safe
                        way. Flat pack kindness at its best.</p>
                </div>

            </div>
